caption: Nice and cozy little place with great food and service.  One person in our party was a vegetarian and had no problems fining a couple options to choose from.  Great wine list and nice sized portions.  Our server was very familiar with the menu and made some great recommendations.  Can't wait to go back.
Great service and really good food

Lively atmosphere (although borderline raucous), typical of a weekday upscale bar spot. Best deal in the house is definitely the 4-beer flight for $11.  Highly recommend the Aged Pimento Cheese with Shrimp Crackers and Bolognese. The Steak was unfortunately tough despite being done medium rare.

This gastropub offers very delicious spins on surprisingly healthy dishes (unhealthy dishes are also available), as well as a solid array of cocktails, wine, and local craft beers. The octopus is a very well crafted and highly recommended dish, and the shishito peppers are filled with ample flavor.
